    <name>
      <text>Adding logarithms for mixed power and root</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>The quantity of Manganese in a Physics experiment is given by:
</p>

<p>
\[
{@base@}^{@exp@} \times \sqrt{{@base@}}
\]
</p>

<p>
By applying logarithms, write \(\!\left({@base@}^{@exp@} \times \sqrt{{@base@}}\right)\) in terms of \(\log {@base@}\).
</p>

<p>
[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]
</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
First rewrite the square root as a fractional index:
</p>

<p>
\[
\sqrt{{@base@}} = {@base@}^{1/2}
\]
</p>

<p>
Now combine the powers:
</p>

<p>
\[
{@base@}^{@exp@} \times {@base@}^{1/2}
= {@base@}^{@exp + 1/2@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Apply the logarithm law:
</p>

<p>
\[
\log(a^n) = n\log a
\]
</p>

<p>
So,
</p>

<p>
\[
\log\!\left({@base@}^{@exp@} \times \sqrt{{@base@}}\right)
= ({@exp@} + \tfrac{1}{2})\log {@base@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the correct answer is:
</p>

<p>
\[
\boxed{({@exp@} + \tfrac{1}{2})\log {@base@}}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
